'''Halmir''' ({{FA|390}} - {{FA|471|n}}) was the son of [[Haldan]] and the lord of the [[Men of Brethil|People of Haleth]] in [[Brethil]]<ref>{{WJ|West}}, ''(iii) The Haladin''', p. 237</ref> at the time of the [[Dagor Bragollach]] ("Battle of Sudden Flame").<ref>{{S|Index}}</ref> He was the father of [[Haldir (Chieftain of the Haladin)|Haldir]], [[Hundar]], [[Hareth]] and [[Hiril]].

== History ==
After the Dagor Bragollach, and the capture of [[Minas Tirith in Beleriand|Minas Tirith]], [[Orcs]] began to roam unhindered across the lands of [[West Beleriand]]. Halmir called on the aid of King [[Thingol]], who sent many stout [[Sindar]]in warriors under the command of [[Beleg]] to his aid. Together, Halmir and Beleg destroyed a legion of invading Orcs, and gave the southern lands a respite from the defeats in the north.<ref>{{S|Fingolfin}}</ref>  

Halmir joined the [[Union of Maedhros]] but died before the [[Nirnaeth Arnoediad|next battle]]. He was succeeded as leader of the [[Haladin]] by his son, [[Haldir (Chieftain of the Haladin)|Haldir]].<ref>{{S|Fifth}}</ref>

